President Obama spoke with Ukrainian President Petro Poroshenko about the ongoing crisis in eastern Ukraine. They both expressed their support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. They agreed that any Russian intervention in Ukraine without Ukraine's consent would be unacceptable and a violation of international law. President Poroshenko mentioned the continued shelling of Ukraine's territory from Russia. He also updated President Obama on his engagement with the International Committee of the Red Cross to deliver humanitarian aid to the affected populations in eastern Ukraine. President Obama stressed the urgency of these efforts and encouraged President Poroshenko to exercise restraint and caution in military operations to avoid civilian casualties. They both agreed that diplomatic efforts should be prioritized to find a political resolution to the crisis.